# Security & Hardening — Three-Tier Boundary System

## ALWAYS DO (no exceptions)

- Validate all external input at API boundaries
- Parameterize all database queries — never concatenate user input into SQL
- Use framework auto-escaping for output
- Hash passwords with bcrypt/scrypt/argon2
- Use httpOnly, secure, sameSite cookies for sessions
- Run `pip-audit` or `safety check` before releases

## ASK FIRST (requires human approval)

- Adding new authentication flows
- Storing new categories of sensitive data
- Adding new external service integrations
- Changing CORS configuration
- Modifying rate limiting

## NEVER DO

- Commit secrets to version control (API keys, passwords, tokens)
- Log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, full credit card numbers)
- Trust client-side validation as a security boundary
- Use `eval()` or equivalent with user-provided data
- Expose stack traces or internal error details to users
